        h5 Never been to a hackathon?

        p.
          Great! We'd love to have you. If you're unfamiliar with the format, a hackathon
          is a day long (or two), intensive learning and building session often
          organized around a theme, like ours, transparency and feedback in government.

        p.
          Our hackathon is constructed with a fun, cooperative atmosphere, so if you
          aren't an expert coder or you're just starting to learn design you'll
          be just as welcome as a twenty year veteran of the scene.

        p
          a.alt(href="https://medium.com/@tfogo/hackathons-are-for-beginners-77a9c9c0e000#.f3aerpjej", target="_blank") Check out this article on Medium for an introduction to hackathons.

        h5 Code of Conduct

        p.
          We take making the Nashville Civic Hack Day a safe place for people to
          get together very seriously. Please read our code of conduct, and don't
          hesitate to contact us if you have questions, concerns, or experience
          any uncivilized behavior during the event.

        p.u-text-center
          a.link-button.button.large.u-text-center(href="//hackcodeofconduct.org/nashvillecivichackday", target="_blank") Read the Code #[span.display-560 of Conduct]

        h5 Accessibility

        p.
          We're ironing out the details of the venue, and as soon as we know what's up,
